## Commit Conventions

This project follows [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/).
{%- if cz_gitmoji %} Commits also use [Gitmoji](https://gitmoji.dev/) prefixes for visual categorization.{% endif %}

Examples:

```
{% if cz_gitmoji -%}
✨ feat: add new feature
🐛 fix: resolve bug in parser
📝 docs: update API documentation
{%- else -%}
feat: add new feature
fix: resolve bug in parser
docs: update API documentation
{%- endif %}
```

[Commitizen](https://commitizen-tools.github.io/commitizen/) is configured to help you write correctly formatted commit messages.
{% endif %}
## Documentation

Documentation is built with [MkDocs](https://www.mkdocs.org/) and [Material for MkDocs](https://squidfunk.github.io/mkdocs-material/).

To serve docs locally:

/// tab | make
```bash
make docs-serve
```
///

/// tab | mise
```bash
mise run docs:serve
```
///

API documentation is auto-generated from docstrings using [mkdocstrings](https://mkdocstrings.github.io/).
